      "bezeichnung": "Matlab",
      "lernziele": "<p>Participants are able...</p>\n<ul>\n<li>...to trace, explain, write and modify program codes.</li>\n<li>...to organize program codes into files (scripts and functions), and they use a source code version control system.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<ul>\n<li>Fundamentals of MATLAB programming</li>\n<li>Problem decomposition, Functions, Copilot</li>\n<li>Control structures: conditionals &amp; loops</li>\n<li>Arrays, Indexing</li>\n<li>Plotting, Debugging</li>\n<li>Git (source code version control)</li>\n<li>File operations</li>\n<li>Image processing</li>\n<li>Applications&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
      "bibliographie": "<p>MATLAB basics are found in many books and internet resources. For instance, this course covers large parts of:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Chapman, S.: Essentials of MATLAB programming, 3rd edition, 2018, chapters 1 to 5.</p>",
